Paul Frederick White, FANZCA is a researcher in anesthesiology, Director of Research at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center at Los Angeles, retired professor and the holder of the Margaret Milam McDermott Distinguished Chair of Anesthesiology at The University of Texas Southwestern Medical Center at Dallas, and the author and editor of several journals and textbooks on the subject. With over 350 peer-reviewed publications and authorship in 9 anesthesiology textbooks, White has helped shape and revolutionize the field of ambulatory anesthesia and intravenous anesthesia.
